# Clerk Authentication & Data Isolation

All authentication in this project is handled by **Clerk**. Users must only ever be able to access their own data. Never trust client-supplied user IDs — always derive the authenticated user's ID from Clerk on the server side.

## Getting the Current User

### In Server Components and Route Handlers (App Router)

```ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { userId } = await auth();

if (!userId) {
  // User is not authenticated — redirect or return 401
}
```

### In Client Components

```tsx
import { useAuth } from "@clerk/nextjs";

const { userId } = useAuth();
```

## Data Access Rules

- **Always** retrieve `userId` from Clerk (`auth()` on the server, `useAuth()` on the client) — never accept it as a parameter, query string, or request body value.
- **Always** filter database queries by the authenticated `userId` to ensure users can only read or modify their own records.
- **Never** expose data belonging to other users, even if the caller supplies a valid-looking ID.
- **Never** skip the authentication check — all API routes and Server Actions that access user data must verify the user is signed in first.

## Examples

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — Server Action: create a deck scoped to the authenticated user
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decksTable } from "@/db/schema";

export async function createDeck(name: string, description: string) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

  await db.insert(decksTable).values({ userId, name, description });
}

// ✅ GOOD — Route Handler: fetch only the current user's decks
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decksTable } from "@/db/schema";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";

export async function GET() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId)
    return NextResponse.json({ error: "Unauthorized" }, { status: 401 });

  const decks = await db
    .select()
    .from(decksTable)
    .where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));

  return NextResponse.json(decks);
}

// ❌ BAD — trusting a user-supplied ID from the request body
export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { userId, name } = await req.json(); // ❌ never trust this
  await db.insert(decksTable).values({ userId, name });
}

// ❌ BAD — fetching all decks without filtering by user
const allDecks = await db.select().from(decksTable); // ❌ exposes every user's data
```

## Middleware

Ensure `proxy.ts` is configured to protect routes using Clerk's `clerkMiddleware`:

```ts
// proxy.ts
import { clerkMiddleware, createRouteMatcher } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const isPublicRoute = createRouteMatcher(["/", "/sign-in(.*)", "/sign-up(.*)"]);

export default clerkMiddleware(async (auth, req) => {
  if (!isPublicRoute(req)) {
    await auth.protect();
  }
});

export const config = {
  matcher: ["/((?!_next|.*\\..*).*)"],
};
```
